The following is a text message conversation between Elizabeth ‚ÄúLibby‚Äù Dixon and ‚ÄúBronco,‚Äù sent over a period of two months prior to Libby‚Äôs disappearance.
Remember, don‚Äôt use my real name, okay?
You got this prepaid phone and I told you I‚Äôd delete our texts as we go‚Äî
I‚Äôm sorry ‚Äî I hate texting you.
I just think it‚Äôs safer to speak on the phone.
Then there‚Äôs no paper trail or whatever.
I don‚Äôt have a bedroom door, babe.
If I call you right now, my dad will hear me.
Okay, then no specifics in our texts.
No one‚Äôs gonna find out about us.
I kinda can‚Äôt believe we‚Äôre pulling this off.
Yeah. If you keep telling him you‚Äôre at Rachel‚Äôs house when you‚Äôre really with me, he‚Äôs gonna figure it out, sooner or later.
He thinks me and Rachel are working on a science project.
I told him we‚Äôre studying anatomy‚Ä¶
Plus, he‚Äôs been really wrapped up in his charity stuff lately.
Don‚Äôt you feel a little guilty about our relationship, though?
Hell, no. I think sneaking around makes it hotter.
I wanna be bad with you.
So‚Ä¶do you wanna hook up tomorrow?
Absolutely. Meet me at the spot where we ate those corn dogs.
God, they were so gross. I‚Äôll bring the food this time.
I‚Äôll get you some more of the wine coolers you liked.
Oh, yeah, like that Lady Gaga song.
I keep thinking that your codename makes you sound like a cowboy.
Maybe I should call you Pistol Pete, too.
I wanna hear your voice, babe.
Okay, well, I get off work at 9.
I can call you on the way home if that‚Äôs cool?
Mom‚Äôs making me help cook dinner.
I‚Äôll call you after the fam goes to bed, okay?
Fam‚Äôs at church, obvs ‚Äî and they‚Äôre going out to eat after, so that‚Äôll take some time.
I faked a stomachache to stay home.
Meet me at The Tree in 20.
I‚Äôll bring some snacks and stuff.
I still think the field is kind of risky, babe‚Ä¶
Don‚Äôt be paranoid ‚Äî it‚Äôs hidden by that row of big trees.
It‚Äôs in the middle of nowhere.
Yeah, but it‚Äôs still out in the open.
Besides, the risk makes it sexy, doesn‚Äôt it?
It‚Äôs so hot out, too. I might have to take off some clothes to keep cool‚Ä¶
I‚Äôm at home alone. Can I call you?
Let me clock out for my break. Call me in 10?
I think you‚Äôre prettier than her, babe.
It‚Äôs a song, silly. Makes me think of you.
I think of you whenever I hear that song by Pink Floyd.
‚ÄúSeveral Species of Small Furry Animals Gathered Together in a Cave and Grooving with a Pict.‚Äù
Yeah, it‚Äôs a real song, babe.
I wish you could be here.
I thought you were gonna dump him?
He gets really mad about small stuff.
I don‚Äôt know what he‚Äôd do to me if I broke it off.
I‚Äôd protect you from that shrimp.
You know he‚Äôs not a shrimp.
I know. I guess I‚Äôm gonna go to sleep now.
Meet me at The Spot in 10?
I did it. I broke up with BF.
OMG. Weren‚Äôt you gonna wait ‚Äòtil school was out for the summer?
I couldn‚Äôt be with him when all I need is you.
There‚Äôs only a week of school left, anyway.
What happened when you told him?
He punched a hole in the bathroom wall.
Yeah. He took me into the men‚Äôs room in the gym.
No one ever uses that bathroom except during PE.
Babe, what did he do to you?
Nothing. He wanted to get some action or whatever, but I pushed him off of me.
I told him we were breaking up.
When he looked like he was gonna hit me, I ducked.
And he hit the wall instead?
Yeah. Then I ran off to the lunchroom and didn‚Äôt see him the rest of the day.
No, I‚Äôm covering for Carter tonight.
I won‚Äôt let him hurt you, babe.
Do you need me to follow you home tonight?
Meet me by the dumpster at 9.
I need you to hold me.
I need to tell you something.
It‚Äôs so romantic over text, ain‚Äôt it?
I don‚Äôt care how we say it.
How come you haven‚Äôt broken up with GF yet?
I wanna be your one and only.
I think you should end it.
Call me soon, bae. Fam went out but I have a ‚Äústomachache.‚Äù
I need to talk to you.
I did it ‚Äî I broke up with GF.
I only wanna be with you, babe.
I got wine coolers to celebrate.
Don‚Äôt move ‚Äî I‚Äôm on my way.
Psycho Ex won‚Äôt stop texting me.
Yeah, I‚Äôve got a Psycho Ex of my own to deal with.
He sent me a dick pic.
As if that‚Äôs gonna make me run back to him.
I wish it were just you and me‚Äî
No Psycho Exes or anybody else.
No dumb laws to keep us from dating.
If we lived like two hours north we could totally be together.
I can‚Äôt wait to be 18 already.
We‚Äôre like Romeo and Juliet, aren‚Äôt we?
The star-crossed lovers of Cedar Creek‚Ä¶
I hope you‚Äôre not suggesting suicide.
Sometimes it does seem like a good idea, if we can‚Äôt be together.
Do you need to go back to the hospital?
I need to talk to you about something.
Meet me tomorrow at the new spot?
The one you told me about.
